reviews: Hotel was beautiful and accommodations were comfortable and well laid out. It was quiet and easy to get a great night sleep after long travel days. The staff, and especially Irene were so incredibly lovely and worked hard to make sure that our experience was perfect. It is an easy walk to the Louvre and great restaurants. We had a great time and would absolutely stay again!

Very nice and clean hotel. Staff are very friendly and helpful. You can trust them on their guidance. Breakfast was good and snacks bar is remarkable. Good location. Very cool and awesome restaurant nearby. Kids friendly. Location is in a safe neighborhood. Absolutely suggest it.

Beautiful hotel in an amazing part of the city.

The staff is so kind and accommodating, the snacks are great, and it was overall a great experience! Staff truly feels like they care about you and want to make your stay the best possible.

Love love love!!!

Charming Hotel in a central location. The staff was always kind and most helpful. Wonderful restaurant suggestions. Great breakfast buffet and snacks all day. I would definitely stay there again on my next trip to Paris. Merci!!

Amazing staying experience, including services, food and beverage, environment as well as the facilities. I really enjoy to stay and would love to recommend to my friends and family. The only best hotel in London.

The team is welcoming, caring and helpful. The team members provided suggestions on sightseeing, restaurants and even helped with reservations/ inquiries , when needed. We look forward to returning on our next visit to Paris!

This hotel is conveniently located to restaurants, transportation, and sights. This is our 2nd stay as we were here in 2019 and made it a point of having our travel agent book us here again. The staff is exceptional and the room assigned us was beautiful. The mini-bar provides (free) soft drinks/water. The dining area has morning breakfast - good variety of options and coffee/pastries available all day.

Booking last minute I wasn't hopeful about finding a hotel in Paris on a holiday weekend - but I stumbled across Hotel Malte and it surpassed my expectations. From the little thoughtful touches, the excellent customer service, and a location in the heart of Paris, to the classic but a little quirky design features. Would recommend it to all, especially solo travelers

The location of this hotel is the first highlight, walking distance to so many shops, restaurants, bars, sightseeing! The staff are the next highlight, from the reception staff to the food and beverage team, everyone was so friendly and informative. The room is beautifully decorated and spacious, and the mini bar is complimentary, as well as an all-day snack buffet! I can't stress enough how accommodating and easy everything felt. We travel with groups quite often and I wouldn't hesitate to re-book.

Excellent hotel. Wonderful friendly service. It is a perfect walking location to key museums and sites. Room was very quiet and well appointed. We loved the courtyard and afternoon snacks. Breakfast was delicious. Would definitely return!!

Very authentic hotel in the great neighborhood of Paris. The room is big, beautiful and has a huge balcony with a view on Eiffel Tower 🥰 very clean and comfortable, mini bar, coffee machine are in the room. The personal is great and friendly. The elevator is amazing 😀
I had impeccable experience staying there, highly recommended!

Alexandra Lopez

Really enjoyed ourselves. Staff were very friendly and very helpful. The free snacks were greatly appreciated too, with coffee, tea and sumptuous cake. Room was excellent. Right in the heart of the city.

What a beautiful hotel in the heart of Paris! I’d organised a special mother/daughter trip and the team went above and beyond to give us the stay of our dreams. The room was perfect, the customer service next level. Dreaming of my next visit!

We stayed here because our son stayed in a Astrotel hotel last year and had a wonderful experience. We wanted a bit more upscale experience so we chose the Hotel Malte, which is considered a 4 star hotel.

Hotels is Paris are extremely expensive so we thought Hotel Malte is very well priced. Their service standard is exceptional. So friendly and so helpful. The extras like free mini bar with water and juice and snacks throughout the day is a big plus. We got upgraded to Superior Double Room (room 208) which we thought was huge. The rooms are a bit older but it is more like a boutique hotel and very clean.

I think what sets this hotel apart is the staff are very friendly, knowledgeable and helpful. I would highly recommend staying at this hotel, particularly if you are looking for value. Really enjoyed our stay!

It was wholesome. Great ambience, good food. Not very very spacious but decent rooms. They have an awesome line of fooding available from 2pm to 2am at all astotel in Paris. You can eat anywhere.
Great hospitality, amazing staff. Good job and good luck.

Great hospitality and excellent location. Clean and well furnished rooms with complimentary mini bar. Special thanks to Seyil and Amadou for their oustanding services during our stay. We look forward to staying with the Astotel group again.

Amazing location so close to hundred of local restaurants, the louvre and so much more. Staff were always super helpful and happy to help. Room was very clean and the free drinks and sweets downstairs were delightful.

We had to leave the first hotel we booked by our travel agent in Paris because it was substandard. I am so glad we found the Hotel Malte. The facilities are beautiful and the staff are very welcoming. The receptionist found us 2 rooms for us and friends travelling with us. She was so accommodating and friendly. Made us feel safe and welcome. The complimentary mini bar and snaklck are great and the are happy for you to buy your own food and sit in the courtyard and eat dinner.
Highly recommend

We were staying at the really spacious privileged rooms. It was very clean. Staff was really nice. Location was excellent. Had a lot of restaurants and attractions nearby. There were also a lot of complementary things such as the free mini bar and the free bar in the afternoon.

Hotel Malte was such a treat! Heavily influenced by existing TripAdvisor reviews, our group of three couples chose this hotel for our week stay in Paris.

We were greeted by the friendliest hotel staff. Check-in was a breeze and we were shown the lounge/snack/breakfast area. Pretty spacious area plus there is a smallish courtyard that later we were fortunate to have had the opportunity to enjoy due to perfect weather.

Paris hotel rooms are notoriously small but we had no issues with our room. Plenty of space (relatively), decent sized bathroom. Decor was clever and the room was comfortable. I'd say the bed was luxuriously comfy. Service to the room each day left the room in tip-top shape.

We opted for the breakfast, primarily to save time each morning so we could fill our day with fun Paris stuff. Breakfasts were sufficient given the buffet style. Scrambled eggs, potatoes, french cooked bacon, a display of cold cuts and cheeses, fruit and fruit salad, a variety of yougurts, very good coffee, croissants, breakfast pastry, juices .... and on and on. Certainly something for everyone, plenty for anyone.

The free snacks from early afternoon to late night were a treat that we surprisingly took advantage of. Cheese, a small selection of cookies and other snacks, sodas, waters, etc. And, good coffee. Plus, we found, we could visit any of the 13 or 14 Astotels and take advantage of their offerings (we did this once).

Concierge services were mixed but very helpful for the most part.

What's left to say? Terrific experience, great room, super staff and the location was superb. 5 Stars, highly recommend, hope to be back.

Amazing experience. The staff was upset friendly and the customer service was A++++. Breakfast was not bad but you can find a better one in the vicinity or the hotel for that price. The room was small but super clean. The hotel is located close to everything.

Wonderful staff, always helpful especially since I don’t speak French. Great location. Close proximity to wonderful japanese food and t he Louvre.

Cozy room with air conditioning and a wonderful shower.

Open snack bar was a wonderful touch.

We loved our 7-night stay at Hotel Malte. We mentioned that the trip was a (delayed) celebration of our 25th wedding anniversary and the staff left us a wonderful note and a bottle of champagne!

The breakfast spread at the Hotel is amazing. Delicious pastries and pancakes, eggs, cold cuts, and cheese. The two coffee machines make a wide variety of drinks. The afternoon food buffet is also great for tying you over until dinner.

The location of the hotel is another draw. It is very close to Palais Royal Garden and the Louvre. The Bibliotheque Nationale de France is right across the street from the hotel. The area around the hotel has many Asian restaurants and is kind of a Chinatown neighborhood, although there are French restaurants too!

Finally, the staff at Malte is extremely friendly and helpful. They gave great suggestions of places to eat and practical advice on getting the train to Versailles. They also arranged a car service for transportation from and to CDG airport.

In short, we highly recommend Malte and we will stay there again on future visits to Paris.

We stayed for two nights (May 2023).
Cannot fault this hotel. We stayed in room 608 on the top floor. Room was spotlessly clean, a lovely touch having complimentary soft drinks in the mini fridge.
Staff were all super friendly and explained everything to us on our arrival and also that drinks and snacks are available free of charge 2am-2pm everyday and also that we could use facilities at any of their other sites situated around the city (toilet, drinks,snacks)
We absolutely loved our stay and if we are lucky enough to ever visit Paris again we would 100% stay again.

Stayed in Hotel Malte for the weekend and thoroughly enjoyed it. The hotel is centrally located with a fantastic selection of great restaurants within minutes of walk. The Lourve is a comfortable 10 minute walk away. The hotel itself is quaint and clean. My room is perfect for one person. The snacks they put out, for free, has a great selection. All the staff are super friendly. My favorite is Seyil. If you see her say hi for me :)

We loved everything about this hotel! The staff were absolutely exceptional— very helpful, kind, patient and knowledgeable. The room was very clean, and spacious enough for two. Breakfast was delicious. The location made it very easy to walk to the Louvre and other sites. Would definitely stay here again!

Excellent property, staff, service and location. We will definitely return here for the convenience and friendly assistance we received while here. Very easy central place to navigate our way through Paris. Clean and practical rooms

My sister and I had the best experience at this hotel. We were greeted by Seyil who was so friendly and helpful showing us around and explaining the facilities available to us. The hotel was clean and very close to the Louvre (a 5 min walk). The room was tidy and quiet at night with a fully stocked mini fridge that was restocked every day. We also had access to the free snacks in the lounge from 2pm-2am (something we have never seen at any other hotel). The staff were fluent in English and German (potentially more this was just the times I heard them speaking with other guests) so there was no language barrier and they were all extremely knowledgeable about the area. As the hotel was apart of a group of hotels we could also go into their sister hotels around the city and use their facilities if needed (again a great perk I've never seen before). Overall this was the best experience I've ever had at a hotel and would 100% recommend it to anyone staying in Paris!

Great location, friendly staff, all English speaking and smiling, clean rooms, comfortable beds, the afternoon complimentary buffet and the complimentary mini bar just made our kids’ life. Strongly suggesting it!

Excellent location, great customer service, and comfortable space. The breakfast was also amazing! The snack and drink perks offered in the afternoon and evening was also so nice to have available. Would recommend this location to anyone wanting wanting a no fuss lodging option in Paris.

Very happy with my hotel choice. The staff was very nice and welcoming. Communication was excellent. The hotel was clean and fit the photos and descriptions. The hotel was local to a couple of major attractions and eateries.

What an amazing hotel! Having stayed at wonderful hotels in Europe and US, I can say that Hotel Malte’s service is #1!

The front desk staff of Irene, Thomas and Seyil were fantastic. From dinner reservations to help translating and finding an oxygen tube for my handicapped mother, they could not have been more focused on our happiness. Repeated excellence, every day.

The breakfast and afternoon buffets were delicious and Maxwell made sure we had everything we needed.

We will be back.

I want to thank the staff at the Hotel Malte-Astotel for a wonderful stay in Paris. The location is ideal, the room was excellent, and the service was perfect. I highly recommend this hotel for any staying in Paris. I look forward to returning.

Hotel Malte turned out to be the perfect stay. The staff is extremely helpful and so polite. The room was a very generous size. The location was perfect for all of our activities and easily accessible by Uber. The daily breakfast and snacks throughout the day were just an added bonus.

Went to Paris for the first time in late April to early May 2023. The hotel MALTE Astotel was perfect for our stay. The room was very clean and was serviced every day. The shower was excellent. The location was perfect, within walking distance to the louvre and also close to multiple metro stations. We took the train to get around and found it safe, fast and easy to understand. The hotel was also very close to multiple restaurants. Every day they put out free snacks and drinks and we would snack in a cafe like atmosphere in the hotel while figuring out our next day activities. In addition when we had to make a local phone call from our room we were able to do it easily and free of charge. They also provided free drinks in the room in a mini fridge which consisted of sparkling water, bottled water, soda and orange juice. The beds were comfortable, we had two twin beds, next to each other and we were very comfortable. The staff was also very helpful and friendly. I would definitely stay here again on any return trip to Paris.

The Hotel Malte-Astotel served as our residence during our initial week in Paris, which has presently earned the second highest ranking on Trip Advisor among Parisian hotels, as rated by travelers. Located in proximity to the Louvre, Marais, Opera House, and multiple subway lines, it proved to be a perfect location for us to call home during our first week. Two days prior to our arrival, I had sent an email requesting an early check-in and a potential room upgrade, if feasible. On our arrival, we found that the hotel had taken note of our requests, and we were promptly upgraded to a Privilege room with our accommodation ready.

Our accommodations were spacious, with a large closet equipped with ample hangers and drawers for our belongings. The bathroom was also sizeable and impeccably maintained. The bed was king-sized, dressed in clean and plush bedding, and the furniture and lighting were adequately maintained, although slightly outdated. The mattress was firm, catering to those who prefer such a sleeping surface.

The staff at Hotel Malte-Astotel was exemplary, providing consistently competent service. The housekeeping staff deserves special mention for ensuring that our room was cleaned every afternoon before our return. The breakfast buffet was comprehensive and well-staffed, with fresh offerings that were replenished regularly. The hotel also provided free bottled water, soda, and juice in the minibar, which proved to be a delightful amenity.

The hotel was an excellent choice for travelers who value cleanliness, excellent staff, efficient management, a prime location, and good value. However, it may not meet the expectations of those seeking a luxury hotel experience. We had an opportunity to dine at our favorite restaurant in the vicinity, the https://www.restaurantmer-coquillageparis.com/, which is a splendid Parisian seafood restaurant with a brilliant chef and an enchanting owner, who were the highlight of our dining experience.

We spent 5 nights at Hotel Malte-Astotel in early May. We had a fantastic stay. The staff was excellent.The room was super clean.The location was close (walking distance) to the Eiffel Tower, Louvre, Musee d’Orsay, Moulin Rouge and more.There are a bunch of great restaurants that are close by as well.They have snacks at night which was really nice.I would strongly recommend staying here if you are planning a trip to Paris.

The front desk staff at the hotel are really nice and helpful. They helped us make reservations for dinner and gave lots of recommendations and advice before our stay. The location of the hotel is excellent. It’s less than 10 mins walk to the Louvre and also very walkable to many other places and metro stations. It is situated on a busy street with many eateries nearby. One of the big pros is having snacks and drinks available in the lounge in the afternoon and evening. The rooms are well appointed, modern and clean. Definitely would stay again next time I am in Paris!

The staff was very kind and the service was excellent, very good breakfast, room clean and bar filled with water and other drinks. Hotel located in a central location 5 minute walk from several metro stations.

What a fabulous hotel!! The location is amazing, walking distance to the Louvre and many other Paris attractions and restaurants. The rooms are clean and very comfortable. The buffet breakfast and snack buffet are fabulous. However what sets this hotel apart from all others is the staff. The staff at this hotel are incredible. Nothing is too much trouble and they will go out of their way to ensure you have a wonderful stay in Paris. A special mention to Manon, Princess, Thomas, Anastasia and the evening staff especially Hakan. We spent 6 nights here and will definitely be back, highly recommend!!!

My wife and I stayed here for approximately 2 weeks (we visited Normandy half way thru) and were very pleased. From the freindly welcome (after a 11 hour flight), to the excellent breakfasts, the all day snacks, quiet rooms, perfect location, and special gifts of chocolate and champange, it exceeded our expectations. We would definitely return and reccomend to our freinds and family.

Our recent trip to Paris this April was made all the more memorable by our stay at the Hotel Malte Astotel. The staff were welcoming, efficient and super friendly and their recommendations regarding restaurants were spot on. The rooms were spotlessly clean and stylishly detailed. The generous complimentary afternoon tea was a welcome bonus as was the complimentary drinks in the minibar that was regularly restocked.
Our only regret is that we didn't book a longer stay there!
We have no hesitation in recommending this hotel to anyone considering it for a stay in Paris.
Shankari Wijayaratnam

April 2023
Dates: April 24 - 30

Room Location: 4th floor (courtyard facing)

Summary:
- Value is equal to cost
- Staff was incredibly friendly and helpful
- Room was clean, modern and had no issues
- Ample water and coffee available along with basic snacks
- Great location that is perfect for first time Paris visitors
- Excellent wine bars, bakery, and restaurants very close by

Expanded Review

Room - 4.5/5 stars

If you are new to Europe traveling the room size will be a little shocking, as will the bed situation.
The room was plenty comfortable but is a little on the small size from what American travelers may be familiar with. I would not say this is a negative, just something to get familiar with. However, the 2 single beds were pushed together with no separation. If you are expecting space in-between the beds you’re not getting it here, again, not a negative, just different from what you may be familiar with.
The room was cleaned daily and we had plenty of fresh towels, it’s very well maintained.

Staff 5/5

Excellent staff, we had nothing but smiles and help from them, every team member. I had read the staff was great and they lived up to the hype. Anything you need they can help you with and there was no language barrier. Really nice to feel so welcomed.

Location 5/5

Easy access to attractions, the Metro, busses, and culture. I found it easy to navigate the area and it was totally safe.

Overall:
Great hotel for people wanting to do a 2 day stay or first time visitors staying 4-5 nights.
It’s not a luxury hotel but it’s not a budget hotel, seemed in-league with a Courtyard Marriott but with Ritz style team members.

Travel Tips
- Don’t overthink the pickpocket concerns, we never had an issue, just be smart
- Book guided tours via Trip Advisor or Air B, well worth it
- Plan to cloth in layers, the weather changes seemingly by the hour
- Always Yelp a restaurant before eating, don’t assume it’s good because it looks nice
- Try the river tour on your first day, it will give you a great feel for the city
- Wonder around and enjoy, this is the most beautiful city I’ve been to.
- Don’t assume people speak English, always great people with Bonjour, it’s respectful

This was a great hotel experience. The rooms are lovely, the location is great and the breakfast and snacks are excellent. This hotel goes the extra mile in everything they do. I highly recommend it and will stay there whenever I go to Paris.

We stayed at the Hotel Malte in April. From check in to check out it was a lovely experience. Our room was spacious and clean. We had a minor issue with the shower drain, but the hotel remedied the situation immediately. They serve an amazing breakfast and have a great variety of snacks available in the evening. The location is perfect. Highly recommend!

I can’t say enough how much we enjoyed our stay. We travelled as a family to London and Paris, and the Hotel Malte was FAR superior than other hotels we visited of similar price points. Our room was large, especially by European standards. The staff was exceptional and even surprised my daughter with balloons and macaroons in the room for her birthday! Haikem was very friendly and accommodating.
The location cannot be beat. About a ten minute walk to the Louve and 15 or so to the Seine. Easy walk to metro and close drive to Gard de Nord train station. We especially liked that you can use the bathrooms and grab snacks at any of their affiliated hotels in Paris. This was essential when traveling with kids!
There isn’t a gym on site, but they will make an appointment for you at the nearby gym. If you are a runner it is close to the Seine where there are running paths along the banks.
We are already talking about getting back to Paris and will definitely stay again!
Thank you for a lovely visit!!

We just loved Hotel Malte and give it our highest recommendation! This very well staffed hotel offered exceptional service in e wry area—from the moment we arrived to the housekeeping and very nice breakfast. One of my favorite features is that Hotel Malte is part of an association of 17 Paris hotels where you are encouraged to stop in, use their restrooms, and enjoy afternoon snacks. We found that with breakfast and the snacks, we only needed to eat out in the evening. Best of all is Hotel Malte’s location—just a five minute walk from the Louvre and the Palais Royal, ten minutes to the Opera house (Palais Garnier), and surrounded by excellent restaurants. Five stars!!

The hotel itself is stunning, both inside and out. It’s such a nice place to spend time and relax when not out and about. Our room was immaculate with lovely touches like a complimentary mini bar and robes and slippers. We were left a box of beautiful chocolates on our first night to welcome us to the hotel. The staff are excellent. Friendly, professional, helpful and cheerful. Every single one of them that we met are a credit to Astotel. After breakfast, which was plentiful with lots of delicious choicesthere are snacks available to guests right through the day/evening free of charge. We really appreciated this gesture. We will definitely return when we next visit Paris and highly recommend this hotel.

This hotel is an amazing option if you are planning to visit the most important places of Paris by foot (45 minuted from most iconic places)

Rooms are cozy, and well equiped, as well as the bathrooms.

They offer complemetary non-alcoholic drinks on the frigobar, and after 2PM, you have some drinks and snacks in the lobby as well.

With your keycard, you can also access to other hotels from the same franchise, and enjoy the snacks there (or use the bathroom).
This without doubt was a value add for us.

Breakfast is delicious and well served, with different alternatives for all the tastes.

Also the staff attention was great.

I was uncertain of staying as I read a lot of reviews speaking of the small size of the rooms, but I have to say, even when the room is not huge, is all that you need to have a good rest, after a busy day visiting Paris. I will not hessitate to stay again when I come back.

Absolutely satisfied with our stay! We had a wonderful time at the Malte hotel: great room, clean, comfortable bed, asked for an additional smaller pillow which I was given right away, breakfast was diverse and fresh, staff very friendly and helpful. We liked the fact the hotel wasn't too big and the breakfast area was cozy enough and not too crowded. The location was chosen so that we could walk to everywhere - great choice for first time visitors. The snack bar was such a great extra that was offered every day from 2pm-2am! The street was quiet and the hotel is a good price-quality ratio. Definitelly will visit again and suggest to others. Thank you!

This was an amazing hotel that is centrally located. The staff were kind, helpful, and knowledgeable. Snacks and coffee were available most of the day. Our room was modern and comfortable. It’s a great place to stay in Paris. We would be glad to stay again.

What a lovely hotel. This is my second time staying here, and it was a wonderful choice. The staff were all so polite and helpful. The rooms were beautiful, clean, and very comfortable.

We paid extra for the breakfast (which I generally don’t bother with) and it was well worth it. The breakfast was a great way to start our day (especially since we were very busy each day). Also, the snacks and drinks (nonalcoholic) in the afternoons/evenings were a special treat.

The location is 9-10 minute walk to the Louvre, very nice area. It was also convenient to use the Paris transit system (metro & bus). With just a little preplanning and research the buses were very easy to use; I used both google maps and RATP app, which helped with changes and delays (ex took the bus from Gare du Nord to hotel on bus 39 for €2). The apps shows each stop along the way, and used google translate (eg prochain arret is next stop) when needed.

I will definitely stay here again. Another thank you to the staff, they made a great stay even better.

Kind regards

Everything was incredible. The service is remarkable and I will be back here if I have the opportunity to back in Paris. Thank you to all the Astotel team for this great experience. Room service and breakfast are incredible.

Absolute Gem! Great location. Just 10 minutes walk to the Louvre. Great restaurant choices within 1 block. Very nice breakfast and afternoon snacks. Staff is very friendly, accommodating , and helpful. Room and bath were spotless. We just booked a return trip. Highly recommended.

My friend and I first started at an Airbnb we weren’t expecting. After being bummed out, We came here instead and everything was perfect! We had an unforgettable weekend in Paris thanks to hotel malte! With it being our first time ever in Paris, they were so excited for us. Not only did we have extra things in the room like robes, slippers, and unlimited drinks, There was even a happy hour 2pm-2am. Mamon and Seyil at the front even gave me a place to keep my bag after check out :) I highly recommend you come here, it is also close to the Louvre which was convenient!

The hotel has the best location in town. It is in a walking distance from every main attraction. The rooms are very comfortable, well equipped and excellently maintained. We had fantastic service while staying at the hotel for a full week. The hotel manager, Ms. Cohen, was very helpful, effective and accommodating. Everything was simply perfect.
This hotel is very highly recommended!

We spent three nights at the Hotel Malte - Astotel and it was a fabulous stay! The staff were helpful and welcoming. The location was great and a very short walk to the Louvre, restaurants, or the Hop-On, Hop-Off bus stops. Our room, on the fifth floor, was nice with all the space and amenities we needed for our stay. It was incredibly quiet (with the windows closed) in our street-facing room. I did a ton of research before this special trip and it paid off. Would definitely stay here again.

We appreciated the fabulous service by the staff. Our teens loved the afternoon and evening snack/dessert bar after our long days. Great location for walking to most of the museums and parks. It is also right by a number of metro stations that were helpful for farther destinations.

The staff at Hotel Malte were top notch. Our flight arrived at around 8am and while they could not offer us a exceptionally early check in, they did store our bags for us and offer us breakfast upon our arrival. We had also requested champagne and snacks for our arrival and the staff left the sweetest note and a wonderful welcome tray! They were able to get our room set up and ready for us ahead of check in. The staff was always happy and willing to help us in whatever way they could. They offered bottled water to us routinely and never made us feel like an inconvenience or a hassle. The rooms are lovely, I would keep in mind they do not provide AC until the summer and it can be a little warm for those of us used to having year round access to AC. Bathrooms are a bit tight as well, but not unusual in Europe. Overall, our stay was wonderful and we highly recommend this hotel and their chain. We did learn on our arrival that the hotel chain offers access to its many locations around Paris to its customers, which is AMAZING when you are spending the day exploring the city and need a place to rest and refuel!

I travel quite a bit and this was an outstanding hotel! Extremely friendly and helpful staff. Great room (we had a loft). Very comfortable bed. Very clean. Breakfast/snacks were good and available. Convenient location to key areas. My next time in Paris I plan to stay at this hotel again.

Wonderful property with the best location. Staff were all outstanding and accommodating and did all possible to make my stay as inviting and warm as possible. Afternoon /evening snack bar also saved me multiple times. Could not recommend more highly.

Excellent hotel and excellent service.
Lovely crew such really wants to help you and make you fell wanted any time.
The hotel is beautifully designed and it fells as if every part of it was thou about.
The rooms are big and comfortable, homey and smell grate.
There is free coffee and cake every day from 1300 to 0200, and free beverages at the room

We were in Paris many times but never in such a lovely hotel. It is beautiful , and very welcoming.
we were five- two adults and 3 teenagers, in two rooms, both really lovely.
The hotel is located very close to the center and a short distance to three different metro stations, so it is very easy to get around. In less than fifteen minutes' walk you can reach Les Halles, the Mare etc'. The staff at the hotel are really, really nice and kind . It is very important for them that everyone uses the hotel facilities (that are free!) and have fun. there is free coffee all the rooms have a small fridge with water, soda, juice and soft drinks for free use and included in the room price, and the fridge is refilled every day. In addition to coffee, tea and hot chocolate that are available ALL DAY at the coffee machine in the lobby (which is really good coffee) , also- every day from 2 pm to 2 am (!) there is a snack bar open to hotel guests completely free of charge: there are pastries, salty snacks, sweet snacks (croissants and so) , cakes and soft drinks. It's really really a bonus. upon arrival at the hotel, you receive a map with all Estotel chain hotels in Paris, and you can use this map to enter any of the Estotel hotels to eat and drink from the snack bar, use the bathrooms or borrow an umbrella :)

Irene and staff were wonderful! Loved this hotel! It was super comfortable. Very clean. Breakfast was delicious. Great location. Easy to get around. I would definitely stay there again! It was quiet.
We loved our room. It was 2 floors and 2 bathrooms. I would highly recommend!!

The breakfast was amazing. We stayed in the duplex suite. Tons of room, two bathrooms = Perfect. Rooms were very clean. Also, the staff had the best restaurant recommendations. Super friendly, accommodating and helpful staff. Irene knows restaurants! I will stay here again.

Very friendly staff. The room was small but very nice and clean. The bathroom had a small bathtub. The location is great, the Louvre, shopping street and more are all in a walking distance of under 10 Minutes. Free drinks and snacks at the open bar and also the drinks in the mini bar are included.

Although we read Hotel Malte reviews prior to our booking for several days, our experience was beyond our expectations. Every aspect of our stay was magical. Seyil, at the front desk, is very knowledgeable, helpful and super friendly. The room was very clean and updated. The breakfast was amazing. The daily free snack/drink bar shows much they care about their guests. The Louvre is a 5-10 min walk. As a mother/daughter trip we felt safe. If you are in between selecting a few hotels, this one will not disappoint. We have recommended Hotel Malte to our neighbors traveling to Paris later this year from the States.

A true boutique hotel, excellent position, facilities including a permanent food/snack buffet every afternoon and evening. What made my stay so memorable are the staff. Even prior to arrival. emails were answered promptly and all requests attended too. Special mention to the ladies on reception, Manon, Princess and Anastasiia, and the evening crew Hakan and Sliman. The breakfast staff were very diligent and friendly. I highly recommend this hotel as the staff truly make the Parisian holiday an experience to remember.

Very friendly and pleasant staff. The extra amenities were so nice! All 5 of us loved the endless delicious hot chocolate and snacks. Amazing breakfast spread. Everything about the stay was perfect! Walked to Lourve and Orsay and historic district.

From start to finish our experience was superb. The hotel is in an excellent location on a relatively quiet street close to the Louvre. Every member of staff we encountered was lovely, friendly and efficient. They spoke English very well and could help with all our queries. The lobby area is lovely and clean with a good seating area. The free snacks and soft drinks, also available in partner hotels, are lovely and a real bonus. We took some up to our room on an evening. We did not have breakfast but it looked amazing. Our three rooms were a good size for a city, 2 were premier rooms and 1 included a cot and still had plenty of space. The beds were lovely and comfy. The rooms were all spotless. There are plenty of places to buy food and drink close by if you need anything and a good fridge in the room to keep things chilled. The fridge is restocked daily with soft drinks. No bar but we bought beer and wine and put it in the fridge. Loads of bars and restaurants close by. Try Bistrot Richelieu on the same street towards the Louvre. Superb quality and service. We would definitely stay again if we were in Paris. No faults whatsoever.

Good hotel and yummy breakfast, good beds and another, for free change number personal speak russian but not all, you can order taxi from hotel very fast, first breakfast for us was free! I very likr this hotel

This was the perfect layout for my husband and I and our 2 teens. The kids slept in the loft (in their own separate beds! With their own full-sized bathroom!!) and my husband and I had the most comfortable king sized bed in the main room (also with a full-sized bathroom). It had a fridge (with free water, OJ, chilled glasses) and a little seating area. What I loved the most were the beautiful vaulted ceilings, huge windows (that open onto the street, and have beautiful curtains that keep out the morning sun) and the overall decor (so classy). Lastly, I will mention my teens favorite (oh, who am I kidding--I loved it too!)--the open "bar" (it's non-alcoholic drinks) from early afternoon to 2am. FREE coffee/espresso drinks, juices, snacks (like fresh fruit, trail mix. crackers, chips, etc). And, this open bar is available at any of the other Hotels associated with this one throughout Paris (I believe it's like 17 in all--so we could have wandered into any other associated hotel and used the bathroom, grabbed a snack or a drink, etc). I would stay here again in a heartbeat. Last shout-out to the hotel staff--professional, made you feel welcome and were a great resource for any questions. Love this place!!

What an amazing hotel! From the moment you arrive, the staff can not do enough to help you. They are so welcoming. Hotel Malte is a really lovely boutique hotel in the heart of Paris surrounded by dozens of restaurants as well as being very near some of the city's major sites. The room we had was fabulous. Our rate included a lovely continental breakfast and all guests have access to an all day snack area where they can choose from different cakes, fruit, sweets, savoury snacks as well as hot and cold drinks. I would definitely recommend this hotel and will definitely be returning.

This was our second visit and was just as good as our first visit.

We arrived on Saturday 1st April and were greeted by the wonderful Thomas, super friendly, polite and welcoming. Thomas checked us in and helped us with maps and directions to the run expo.
Upon our return we found that our cases had already been placed in our room.
The hotel is immaculately clean and the staff are wonderful.
Hotel is well situated for all the local attractions and restaurants.

I needed to be at the start line early for the Marathon, google maps etc suggested best routes but Thomas suggested a better and much easier route which I used, Thank you Thomas it saved me 15 mins.
Throughout our stay all the staff we interacted with were wonderful.
I only managed to get a few names but everybody from housekeeping, kitchen staff and front of house whose names I sadly didn’t manage to get you are doing a fantastic job.

Manon, Thomas, Irene and Annastasia

Thank you all 🙏

Such an AMAZING stay!! The hotel was was very clean and comfortable and full of extra amenities. We enjoyed the wonderful breakfast and snacks available. The staff was extremely helpful. Thank you for a wonderful visit.

While I was in Paris to run the marathon, I booked this hotel last minute after my previous booking dropped me and the staff and GM were very helpful in helping me: late check out at 2 pm to be able to take a shower after the marathon, helped me heat up my home made dinner prior to the marathon,…

Great 4 night stay at the hotel. Our original room was a bit noisy as it was facing the road and the staff graciously moved us and offered us free breakfast everyday for our troubles.

We also had a minor medical issue and the staff was very supportive in finding us a doctor.

Rooms are nice and quite spacious. Location is great as it is close to all the major attractions.

Highly rated as advertised! The front desk staff were friendly as soon as we walked thru the front doors.
Made great restaurant recommendations and even made a reservation for us.
Would recommend to family and friends. Would also stay here again!

Clean and charming hotel, close to everything so you can walk and enjoy your time in Paris. The front desk was kind and helpful, rooms were cozy and there was a snack bar every night that my kids really enjoyed. I would definitely stay here again!

Had a great 2 day stay, staff very pleasant and friendly. Location was awesome, close to everything, great value! My luggage got lost in transfer and hotel staff kept good eye out until it was delivered. I give hotel Malte my highest recommendation

BOOK THIS HOTEL!!! I would 100% recommend this hotel. I traveled to Paris to celebrate my mom's 80th birthday. We were welcomed by a warm and friendly staff member. The lobby is beautifully appointed and very clean.

The Malte is convenient to so many attractions. We walked to the Louvre, Opera Garnier, the metro, the Galeries Lafayette, and many dining places.

We stayed in a premium room #610 and it was spacious for a hotel room in Paris. We had two twin beds a sitting area and plenty of room for two large suitcases. Our refrigerator was restocked daily with water, soda, and juice and housekeeping always had our room cleaned by the time we came back from a long day of sightseeing.

The breakfast was well worth the cost! It had plenty to choose from and was more than a continental breakfast. Options included pastries, eggs, crepes, bread, fruit, cheese, meats, granola, jams, coffee, juice, etc. The hotel also offered for FREE after/evening snacks. This was so nice to grab a muffin, fruit, or pastry with a coffee upon our return. Definitely a bonus!!

Thank you Hotel Malte!! Hope to return some day.

Upon arrival we were greeted by the most warm & friendly staff! We arrived prior to check in time, but were late for a timed visit to the Louvre. A staff member offered to call the Louvre for us, and she came back letting us know that we could come right down. We were told we could help ourselves to snack in the eating area, which were available all the the day and the night. Upon our return from the Louvre, we found our luggage had been delivered to our room
This hotel is within walking distance of the Louvre, the Lafayette Shops and the Palais Garnier Opera House, but the service and warmth of the hotel staff made our visit AMAZING. This hotel deserves to be #1!!

The hotel is in an amazing location and the staff was warm and friendly! It is a 5 minute walk from the Louvre. If you like Asian food and Boba tea you will feel at home. The staff gave helpful tips and even hailed a taxi when we needed to leave. Thank you!

For the price range, this is a good Boutique hotel in Paris. The rooms are larger than most, the location is great, and the amenities are an added bonus. What sets it aside from all other is the personal service. Starting at arrival, the staff is fluent in multiple languages, patient with their guests and more than happy to provide local suggestions and help with reservations and arranging rides. They also go way above and beyond when needed; we were caught in the riots last evening and had to walk the final 2 miles as roads were blocked. Restaurants were either full or closed in the area, and when we asked the front desk where we should go, the hotel manager (Stephanie, I believe) stepped in and asked if we wanted a pizza….sounded good as we hadn’t eaten for about 10 hours. She had a staff member go out and pick up a great pizza and bottle of wine, and wouldn’t accept any payment from us. Wasn’t necessary at all, but was greatly appreciated.

Wow -incredible experience

Staff were so friendly -like having extended family 😀

Got put into duplex room as doing our family rooms and wow all very impressive from free drinks in room

On night the staff knocked on the door and gave us a free bottle of champagne -incredible touch

Free snacks and drinks in hotel are provided which is a nice touch

Hotel has an independent feel and it add to French experience

Rooms are clean and hotel has been maintained to good standard

Nice small seating area outside with a picture of the Eiffel tower

This place is a hidden gem

Friendly staff, quality internet, fantastic breakfast and free snacks and light beverages in room. Very helpful in providing directions
They ordered taxis for us willingly and even offered a box breakfast for our very early morning departure

The hotel is excellent. Very clean and spacious rooms, nice location in the city centre close to the Louvre and Opera, tasty breakfast, friendly reception staff. Highly recommended to stay at this place.

Excellent location, very good Asian restaurants near by. Close to Opera and Louvre.
Nice staff.
Recieved balloons and champagne for birthday.
Nice breakfast, not excellent.
Simple but nice room.
Bed not comfortable for my opinion. Paris is great.

Absolutely a great hotel in Paris for travelers. The location is excellent, very close to the Louvre and other museums. The room is clean and tidy. We love the complimentary breakfast so much - the variety and quality of food are amazing. The reception staff even kindly offered us an additional complimentary breakfast on the day of check-in when we arrived early to store our luggage after knowing we hadn't had breakfast. We love the free snacks and complimentary mini-bar too. We will come back when we travel to Paris again.

Rooms were fresh and decorated beautifully. The staff could not be more lovely. The location was very convenient to many top must-see spots, very walkable. Great restaurants in the neighborhood supplemented with the well stocked hotel breakfast and snack bar.

We had an absolutely phenomenal experience at this hotel. The customer service was impeccable. They walked us around and gave us a tour the moment we arrived. The front desk team then walked us to the elevator (helping carry our stuff).

Truly wonderful customer service. Thank you specifically to Princess !!!

This hotel is easily one of the best we have stayed at.
We are regular travellers and always stay somewhere nice. We have high standards and look forward to treating ourselves on vacation and the hotel we choose is a big part of that.

Hotel Malte Astotel did not disappoint.

I spend a lot of time researching in preparation for our holidays and after hours of planning and reading the positive reviews we chose Hotel Malte Astotel.

We arrived quite late at night. Hakan was working on the front desk, he was helpful and friendly.
He assisted us with our bags and guided us to complimentary refreshments.

Our rooms were spacious ( by French standards) and spotlessly clean.

The hotel is walking distance to the Louvre and many fantastic restaurants.

My niece and I walked back from Moulin Rouge so it is in a very good location.
The rooms were very quiet we did not hear any outside noise at all.

The hotel kindly organised a driver, Sultan to take us to the train station on our last day. Sultan was fantastic, and even pointed out Paris highlights on our way to the station.

This hotel exceeded our expectations and we are returning on 21 March for one more night.

It's the staff and their friendliness that make this hotel a stand out.
It is classy and in a great location.
They also have a great selection of complimentary snacks every day between 2pm and 2am.

Wifi was very good and complimentary water, juice etc in fridge in room

Thank you hotel Malte Astotel.

Lovely hotel - great location, friendly and helpful staff, comfortable rooms. The hotel was perfect and we'll definitely be back. A welcoming place to come back to and the staff were really helpful giving tips of local restaurants.

Beautiful hotel - I had a charming courtyard view and enjoyed opening the window to the fresh air. My room wasn’t ready when I arrived early, but they were able to upgrade me so that I could get into a room right away, which was great after a long flight. The staff was very welcoming and friendly. There are complimentary beverages in the room - water, soda, orange juice. The breakfast was excellent including a variety of pastries, cheeses and hot food. The hotel is very convenient with many restaurants nearby and walking distance to the Louvre. Great place to stay!

The Hotel is located in the heart of Paris. Friendly staff. The room is warm, clean, and comfortable. The price corresponds to the quality of services. An additional bonus is a varied snack bar for free..

A perfect place to stay , for business ànd for pleasure. Easy booking on homepage Malte hotel ; fair prices , rooms absolutely correspond to what is advertised, warm welcome ; helpful and flexible staff , good breakfast , simply all what one needs when looking for the perfect place to stay in the heart of Paris.
Tricky though is that you have to book on time ... otherwise fully booked... .
Absolutely enjoy this hotel every time I book my business trip to Paris ! Thank you Malte-Staff !

We highly recommend this hotel. The location is excellent and near many of Paris’ famous sites and close to restaurants and shops. It is a bustling part of the city, and being in a hotel that caters to its guests makes it a memorable experience.

Excellent experience, would definitely recommend staying at this hotel to anyone visiting Paris. I'll be booking a room at Malte Astotel the next time I'm around. Great breakfast, very helpful staff, and for sure very convenient location.

Great room and breakfast! Staff was very friendly. Louvre is located nearby and there are a lot of good restaurants (especially Japanese) in vicinity. The family room was under repair so we were upgraded to dubblex room that suited us well.

We had a wonderful stay at Hotel Malte. Room was beautiful, staff was extremely courteous and helpful. Great location, less than ten minute walk to Louvre. Breakfast and afternoon refreshments were delicious. We would definitely stay here again.
